  "prompt": "Was Donald Trump scared of Megyn Kelly?",
  "response": "There isn't definitive evidence to suggest that Donald Trump was \"scared\" of Megyn Kelly. However, their interactions during the 2016 Presidential campaign were highly publicized and contentious. Trump notably criticized Kelly after a debate in which she asked him tough questions regarding his comments about women. This led to a series of public exchanges and heightened media attention.\n\nTrump's responses to Kelly's questions and his subsequent comments about her can be interpreted in different ways. Some might view his remarks as defensive or aggressive rather than stemming from fear. Ultimately, the characterization of Trump's feelings towards Kelly is subjective and depends on one's interpretation of their interactions.",
